The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 East Bengal will lock horns with arch-rivals Mohun Bagan in the opening match of the ensuing ONGC Bengal Premier Table Tennis League slated to start from Wednesday at the SAI, Eastern Centre. Six teams, including Mohammedan Sporting, Sports Authority of India (SAI), Rungta Group and STAG are participating in the league. The meet will continue till September 7. Former India skipper P.K. Banerjee, Subrata Bhattacharya and Bula Chowdhury will be present at the inaugural programme at SAI on Wednesday.          
	 The CAB has asked the BCCI to organise this seasons Cooch Behar Trophy final in Cooch Behar. There (in Cooch Behar) we have a good ground It will be a great way to honour the Maharaja of Cooch Behar if we host the final of the national under-19 meet there, CAB joint secretary Amitava Banerjee said on Thursday.                
	FOOTBALL: Sahara CFL Premier Division match  Mohun Bagan vs Railway FC at Mohun Bagan ground 3.30pm                                                                                                                                                                     
